Title: Inadequate Access Control: Admin Can View Another Employer's Pending Contribution Details
Description: An admin user can access and view pending contribution details of other employers, which should be restricted to the respective employer's admin only. This improper access control leads to exposure of sensitive financial data, potentially violating data privacy policies and creating business risks.

Impact:

Exposure of confidential financial information related to contributions.
Risk of privacy breaches, leading to reputational damage and compliance violations.
Misuse of information for competitive or malicious purposes.
Recommendation:

Implement role-based access control (RBAC) to ensure that admins can only view data relevant to their own organization.
Perform access control checks on all endpoints to prevent unauthorized data access.
Conduct regular access control audits and penetration testing to detect and prevent such vulnerabilities.
